'''Tanduay''' originated from the word 'tanguay', an old [[Tagalog]] term for [[peninsula]]. "Tanduay" also means "low-lying land" such as in the case of an entire area in the city of [[Manila]], including the San Miguel and Quiapo districts within the city. The area was once frequently flooded during the wet season leaving some areas exposed including a 'tanguay', which was enclosed by elevated water-levels of estuaries, and which Spanish cartographers referred to as "Isla de Tanduay".

